Introduction

J.You, born as Kim Je-you, is a South Korean rapper and songwriter.

J.You was a contestant in the survival program "WORD KLASS". In the final episode, he ranked first place, allowing him a spot in the boy group TO1 (then known as TOO) under WAKEONE. TO1 debuted on April 1, 2020 with their first mini album "Reason for Being : Benevolence".

On December 17, 2023, WAKEONE announced that all members of TO1, including J.You, chose not to renew their contracts with the agency. Their contracts ended on December 31.
